%N A265275 Least real z > 3/5 such that 1/2 = Sum_{n>=1} {n*z} / 2^n, where {x} denotes the fractional part of x.
%C A265275 This constant is transcendental.
%C A265275 The rational approximation z ~ 51453986933614638386757392337514900843/85070591730234615865843651857942052860 is accurate to many thousands of digits.
%C A265275 This constant is one of 6 solutions to the equation 1/2 = Sum_{n>=1} {n*z}/2^n, where z is in the interval (0,1) - see cross-references for other solutions.
%C A265275 The complement to this constant is given by A265272.
%H A265275 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/DevilsStaircase.html">Devil's Staircase</a>.
%H A265275 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>
%F A265275 The constant z satisfies:
%F A265275 (1) 2*z - 1/2 = Sum_{n>=1} [n*z] / 2^n,
%F A265275 (2) 2*z - 1/2 = Sum_{n>=1} 1 / 2^[n/z],
%F A265275 (3) 3/2 - 2*z = Sum_{n>=1} 1 / 2^[n/(1-z)],
%F A265275 (4) 3/2 - 2*z = Sum_{n>=1} [n*(1-z)] / 2^n,
%F A265275 (5) 1/2 = Sum_{n>=1} {n*(1-z)} / 2^n,
%F A265275 where [x] denotes the integer floor function of x.
%e A265275 z = 0.6048387096774780319162434213958381682946527452380168564858525075890...
%e A265275 where z satisfies
%e A265275 (0) 1/2 = {z}/2 + {2*z}/2^2 + {3*z}/2^3 + {4*z}/2^4 + {5*z}/2^5 +...
%e A265275 (1) 2*z - 1/2 = [z]/2 + [2*z]/2^2 + [3*z]/2^3 + [4*z]/2^4 + [5*z]/2^5 +...
%e A265275 (2) 2*z - 1/2 = 1/2^[1/z] + 1/2^[2/z] + 1/2^[3/z] + 1/2^[4/z] + 1/2^[5/z] +...
